      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDEN GANGSTER (2) crossed over from out wide last start before finishing third (20.16) at this track in a Special conditions race over 342m. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Deserves serious consideration. HERE COMES SHAKA (8) was never in contention last time after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at Gawler (23.09) beating Cool It Miss in a Other on March 29. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. DAME TRUCULENT (1) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Finished in the minors last time when third (19.94) at this track making it back to back placings. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Has good early burn and is suited drawn on the inside. Can measure up. DAWN SAID SO (7) has a solid strike rate at this distance.",
